Subject: [eVuln] WebspotBlogging Authentication Bypass Vulnerability


New eVuln Advisory:
WebspotBlogging Authentication Bypass Vulnerability
http://evuln.com/vulns/41/summary.html

--------------------Summary----------------

Software: WebspotBlogging
Sowtware's Web Site: http://www.webspot.co.uk/
Versions: 3.0
Critical Level: Dangerous
Type: SQL Injection
Class: Remote
Status: Unpatched
Exploit: Available
Solution: Not Available
Discovered by: Aliaksandr Hartsuyeu (eVuln.com)
eVuln ID: EV0041

-----------------Description---------------
Vulnerable script:
login.php

Variable $_POST[username] isn't properly sanitized before being used in a SQL query. This can be used to make any SQL query by injecting arbitrary SQL code.

Condition: gpc_magic_quotes - off

Administrator has an ability to import themes using php code insertion from Admin Control Panel.

System access is possible.

--------------Exploit----------------------
Available at: http://evuln.com/vulns/41/exploit.html


--------------Solution---------------------
No Patch available.

--------------Credit-----------------------
Discovered by: Aliaksandr Hartsuyeu (eVuln.com)


